Create Omnichannel Journeys Using Unified Individual Profiles in Data Cloud
Learn how to set up and use audience activations from Data Cloud to power an omnichannel journey in Marketing Cloud Engagement. This guide walks you through an example of how you can enable an omnichannel experience for your customers. Instead of separate single-channel journeys, users can create seamless customer experiences by using Data Cloud to orchestrate one journey with all Email, SMS, and MobilePush activities together.
Implement a Data Foundation in Marketing Cloud Engagement Using Data from Data Cloud
You can establish a data foundation by activating data from an external system into Marketing Cloud Engagement and linking it to the Engagement Contact Model. You can then refresh and reuse this data across Journey Builder for journey decisioning, wait activities, and exits. You can also use the data for the content personalization of event-triggered campaigns. This solution kit offers a general blueprint on how to set up a data foundation using Data Cloud.
Ingest Google Analytics into Data Cloud
To gain insight into your customer interactions, connect Sales or Service Cloud and Google Analytics data in Salesforce Data Cloud. Enrich your customer information with web engagement data to better segment key audiences and personalize customer interactions.
Ingest Lead Ad Data into Data Cloud
Set up the Lead Capture app to pull leads from Meta (formerly known as Facebook) into Sales Cloud, connect Sales Cloud to Data Cloud, and receive leads into a data lake object (DLO). Having lead information in Data Cloud can help with event orchestration, activation to ad networks, and lead scoring.
Welcome New Loyalty Members to Your Program
Send personalized messages to new loyalty members to educate them on program benefits.
Related Attributes in Activation
Personalize Marketing Cloud Engagement communications using direct and related attributes from Data Cloud. Control the volume and variety of data that can be used in marketing segments.
